1
00:00:07,141 --> 00:00:09,577
⟨Aichan killing my love one after another→

2
00:00:09,643 --> 00:00:12,580
The chase battle is finally reaching its climax⟩

3
00:00:12,646 --> 00:00:18,085
⟨Finally, my buddy Kuroiwa-kun is also involved in the incident⟩

4
00:00:18,152 --> 00:00:21,589
⟨picture? ...I mean, Manami, what are you doing? ⟩

5
00:00:21,655 --> 00:00:24,658
⟨It's not the time for you to get arrested, right?

6
00:00:26,160 --> 00:00:29,096
(Yuriko) Do you want to eat pudding?

7
00:00:29,163 --> 00:00:33,100
(Iori) But I can't seem to get through it... I'm sorry.

8
00:00:33,167 --> 00:00:35,669
(Yuriko) I bought three.

9
00:00:39,173 --> 00:00:42,109
I'm worried, Manami-chan.

10
00:00:42,176 --> 00:00:44,178
(Iori) Yeah...｡

11
00:00:46,680 --> 00:00:49,617
Taking advantage of this incident, Kiryu-kun and Manami-chan →

12
00:00:49,683 --> 00:00:51,619
Is it an accomplice relationship?

13
00:00:51,685 --> 00:00:55,122
The two of them planned a crime together as Ai-chan.→

14
00:00:55,189 --> 00:00:58,192
It seems like that line is emerging.

15
00:01:03,631 --> 00:01:06,567
You shouldn't have done it.

16
00:01:06,634 --> 00:01:08,636
Manami is.

17
00:01:13,641 --> 00:01:15,576
Yeah.

18
00:01:15,643 --> 00:01:18,579
Are you okay, Manami?

19
00:01:18,646 --> 00:01:21,148
I wonder if my heart is broken.

20
00:01:23,150 --> 00:01:26,587
(Manami) Ah! Stuck Stuck!

21
00:01:26,654 --> 00:01:30,090
I'm sure I'll get a prison sentence and lose my job.

22
00:01:30,157 --> 00:01:32,092
Thank you for your hard work.

23
00:01:32,159 --> 00:01:34,595
(Rie) You, be quiet! Seriously.

24
00:01:34,662 --> 00:01:36,664
I'm really excited at this point though.

25
00:01:38,165 --> 00:01:42,102
(Manami) Rie-chan looks like Saiori, the way she speaks.

26
00:01:42,169 --> 00:01:44,605
>>Who is Iori?

27
00:01:44,672 --> 00:01:47,107
Tsk, what a shame!

28
00:01:47,174 --> 00:01:49,610
(Manami) He said something like "It's only because of it"!

29
00:01:49,677 --> 00:01:52,613
They look alike! (Rie) Huh…｡

30
00:01:52,680 --> 00:01:59,620
(Manami) Huh... Iori is my friend.

31
00:01:59,687 --> 00:02:02,623
>> [How do you explain this situation!?]

32
00:02:02,690 --> 00:02:07,061
(Manami) I don't know if you still think of me as a friend.

33
00:02:07,127 --> 00:02:10,064
>> Why are you so depressed?

34
00:02:10,130 --> 00:02:12,566
Next time, if you say anything, I'll punch you!

35
00:02:12,633 --> 00:02:14,568
(Manami) Hohoho...｡

36
00:02:14,635 --> 00:02:17,571
(Tokuta) Please be quiet. (Rie) Oh? What is this?

37
00:02:17,638 --> 00:02:19,573
(Tokuda) Please be quiet. (Rie) Huh?

38
00:02:19,640 --> 00:02:21,575
That's annoying.Are you trying to pick a fight? (sound of door kicking)

39
00:02:21,642 --> 00:02:25,079
Mr. 25, it's interrogation time. Get ready.

40
00:02:25,145 --> 00:02:28,582
(Manami) Yes! Tokuda-san, you look wonderful today too.

41
00:02:28,649 --> 00:02:31,652
>> What's going on emotionally... (Manami) I'll get ready.

42
00:02:33,153 --> 00:02:37,091
Erm... >> Tsk... Ah, it's so weird!

43
00:02:37,157 --> 00:02:42,162
♪～

44
00:02:43,664 --> 00:02:46,600
(Kiyosumi) What are you doing?

45
00:02:46,667 --> 00:02:48,602
(Manami) I was arrested by Mr. Kiyosumi.

46
00:02:48,669 --> 00:02:51,105
(Kiyosumi) It's probably your fault!

47
00:02:51,171 --> 00:02:53,173
[Kuroiwa! ]

48
00:02:55,676 --> 00:02:58,178
[Let me tell you the story]

49
00:02:59,680 --> 00:03:01,115
[Are you listening! ]

50
00:03:01,181 --> 00:03:02,616
[Sound of hitting]

51
00:03:02,683 --> 00:03:05,553
That time I hit you... it hurt.

52
00:03:05,619 --> 00:03:09,056
At that time, if I hadn't punched him, I could have just given him a voluntary interview.

53
00:03:09,123 --> 00:03:11,559
You're really stupid.

54
00:03:11,625 --> 00:03:14,562
(Manami) I was confused. >> Confused…｡

55
00:03:14,628 --> 00:03:17,064
People who get confused and think of punching their boss →

56
00:03:17,131 --> 00:03:19,567
You're too dangerous, aren't you?

57
00:03:19,633 --> 00:03:21,635
(Manami) Sorry.

58
00:03:23,137 --> 00:03:25,573
>> Well, you seem to be doing better than I thought.

59
00:03:25,639 --> 00:03:29,577
(Manami) Well, why don't we stick to this?

60
00:03:29,643 --> 00:03:31,645
>> Well, do your best.

61
00:03:33,147 --> 00:03:36,083
Well...

62
00:03:36,150 --> 00:03:38,586
I have to try my best not to lose.

63
00:03:38,652 --> 00:03:40,588
(Manami) Please do your best. >> Yes.

64
00:03:40,654 --> 00:03:43,090
Shall we go then?

65
00:03:43,157 --> 00:03:46,093
Hey! I'm going to make you spit on me, you bastard.

66
00:03:46,160 --> 00:03:50,097
(Manami) Huh? Another old-fashioned interrogation?

67
00:03:50,164 --> 00:03:52,099
So I...

68
00:03:52,166 --> 00:03:54,101
>> Who is it?

69
00:03:54,168 --> 00:03:56,670
Who fucked you?

70
00:03:59,173 --> 00:04:03,043
You don't do it.

71
00:04:03,110 --> 00:04:08,048
But, to be honest, it's pretty bad.

72
00:04:08,115 --> 00:04:11,118
You're the only suspect.

73
00:04:13,120 --> 00:04:17,558
(Manami) I received a phone call from Kuroiwa-kun just before.

74
00:04:17,625 --> 00:04:19,560
I'll meet Kiryu.

75
00:04:19,627 --> 00:04:21,562
>> I'll believe you →

76
00:04:21,629 --> 00:04:24,565
Even if you head to the scene after receiving Kuroiwa's call →

77
00:04:24,632 --> 00:04:28,569
You'll probably make it in time, based on the estimated time of the crime.

78
00:04:28,636 --> 00:04:31,572
...or else →

79
00:04:31,639 --> 00:04:35,142
Kiryu fucked you?

80
00:04:39,146 --> 00:04:42,082
(Tokuta) Next is the meeting, which lasts 15 minutes.

81
00:04:42,149 --> 00:04:44,585
(Manami) Yes.

82
00:04:44,652 --> 00:04:48,088
Um... What kind of person is Tokuda-san?

83
00:04:48,155 --> 00:04:53,093
>> He's a model prisoner. (Manami) Hohoho~ The sharpness of his jokes is amazing.

84
00:04:53,160 --> 00:04:55,095
>> What?

85
00:04:55,162 --> 00:04:58,599
(Manami) No... seriously...｡

86
00:04:58,666 --> 00:05:03,537
There's a ``serious natural category''... Oh no, I'm a police officer.

87
00:05:03,604 --> 00:05:06,540
>>True face? natural?

88
00:05:06,607 --> 00:05:09,610
(Manami) No, nothing!

89
00:05:11,111 --> 00:05:15,616
>> People who have the courage to change should be fairly evaluated.

90
00:05:17,117 --> 00:05:19,620
I wish you the best.

91
00:05:21,121 --> 00:05:23,057
(Manami) I'll do my best.

92
00:05:23,123 --> 00:05:25,626
...No, I'm not doing anything.

93
00:05:27,127 --> 00:05:29,063
>> Good luck. (Manami) Haha.

94
00:05:29,129 --> 00:05:32,066
I haven't done anything.

95
00:05:32,132 --> 00:05:35,069
Thank you for the book I received.

96
00:05:35,135 --> 00:05:37,571
She's definitely a library person.

97
00:05:37,638 --> 00:05:41,575
(Emoto) I get quite bored at the detention center.

98
00:05:41,642 --> 00:05:44,078
Those with experience will tell you.

99
00:05:44,144 --> 00:05:46,146
(Manami) I learned a lot.

100
00:05:47,648 --> 00:05:50,584
>> ``Midarekami'' is recommended.

101
00:05:50,651 --> 00:05:54,588
I feel like my life is burning in love with Akiko Yosano →

102
00:05:54,655 --> 00:05:57,091
I really can't bear it.

103
00:05:57,157 --> 00:06:00,594
(Manami) Hmm, Akiko is like that.

104
00:06:00,661 --> 00:06:04,098
Hehe, I might cry if I read it now.

105
00:06:05,599 --> 00:06:08,535
>>Are you okay? (Manami) Yeah?

106
00:06:08,602 --> 00:06:11,538
it's okay.

107
00:06:11,605 --> 00:06:15,542
>> It's okay to be a little weaker.

108
00:06:15,609 --> 00:06:20,547
(Manami) Hehe... It's no good if it gets any weaker.

109
00:06:20,614 --> 00:06:25,552
Everyone is hurting because I'm weak.

110
00:06:25,619 --> 00:06:29,056
I don't want you to whine.

111
00:06:29,123 --> 00:06:33,060
I have to press on now.

112
00:06:33,127 --> 00:06:35,062
>> It also gets weaker →

113
00:06:35,129 --> 00:06:38,132
Isn't that one way to hold out?

114
00:06:45,639 --> 00:06:51,145
It's okay to be weak, please stay in a good mood.

115
00:06:57,151 --> 00:06:59,586
(Manami) Thank you.

116
00:06:59,653 --> 00:07:03,590
Really... thank you.

117
00:07:06,593 --> 00:07:09,530
(Wanibuchi) This is the tyranny of power!!

118
00:07:09,596 --> 00:07:12,032
(Tokujii) It was when I entered Sugamo Prison.

119
00:07:12,099 --> 00:07:17,104
(Tokujii) Entered Sugamo Prison... (Manami) I understand.

120
00:07:19,606 --> 00:07:21,542
>> What happened to this?

121
00:07:21,608 --> 00:07:23,544
(Manami) Everyone from My Love came.

122
00:07:23,610 --> 00:07:25,546
When everyone gets excited →

123
00:07:25,612 --> 00:07:28,048
I feel like I really want to get my hands on this place.

124
00:07:28,115 --> 00:07:30,050
>> Is there a detention center?

125
00:07:30,117 --> 00:07:32,553
(Manami) Woohoo...｡

126
00:07:32,619 --> 00:07:36,056
But I'm grateful.

127
00:07:36,123 --> 00:07:41,562
For believing in my innocence and coming this far.

128
00:07:41,628 --> 00:07:44,565
Unlike those two!

129
00:07:44,631 --> 00:07:46,567
>> Just to be clear →

130
00:07:46,633 --> 00:07:49,570
I don't think Manami did it.

131
00:07:49,636 --> 00:07:52,072
(Manami) He had handcuffs out.

132
00:07:52,139 --> 00:07:56,577
>> No, that's because of the situation...!

133
00:07:56,643 --> 00:07:59,079
(Manami) Hmph...｡

134
00:07:59,146 --> 00:08:01,582
>> It's only natural.

135
00:08:01,648 --> 00:08:04,017
(Manami) Ah, it's out! “It’s only because of it.”

136
00:08:04,084 --> 00:08:07,020
Well, that's the line I was given.

137
00:08:07,087 --> 00:08:10,023
That's funny. >> I'm not hitting on you!

138
00:08:10,090 --> 00:08:12,526
Well, well, well, just wait a moment.

139
00:08:12,593 --> 00:08:15,028
We'll try to move in our own way.

140
00:08:15,095 --> 00:08:18,532
(Manami) It's okay... you have work, right?

141
00:08:18,599 --> 00:08:24,538
>> I work to make hot pot. >> That's right.

142
00:08:24,605 --> 00:08:30,043
Once everything is done, let's all have a pot together again.

143
00:08:30,110 --> 00:08:32,112
(Manami) Yeah...｡

144
00:08:40,687 --> 00:08:43,624
>> Hey, who do you meet with every day?

145
00:08:43,690 --> 00:08:45,626
(Manami) Huh?

146
00:08:45,692 --> 00:08:49,129
Eh~ We were friends earlier →

147
00:08:49,196 --> 00:08:51,832
Until yesterday, everyone was my love.

148
00:08:51,899 --> 00:08:54,835
>> My love? (Manami) Ah...｡

149
00:08:54,902 --> 00:08:58,338
It's a little difficult to explain, but...

150
00:08:58,405 --> 00:09:01,842
Well, my favorite people.

151
00:09:01,909 --> 00:09:05,846
>> Ah, a sex friend? What is it? Are you a playboy?

152
00:09:05,913 --> 00:09:10,417
(Manami) It's not like playing or anything...

153
00:09:14,922 --> 00:09:18,859
(Manami) I guess I'm weird.

154
00:09:18,926 --> 00:09:21,461
>> No, I'm not saying it's strange.

155
00:09:21,528 --> 00:09:24,965
(Manami) No... I'm starting to feel weird.

156
00:09:25,766 --> 00:09:30,971
I mean, even though I was hurt so much and even got arrested.→

157
00:09:31,038 --> 00:09:33,974
I don't see any signs of quitting →

158
00:09:34,041 --> 00:09:36,410
Love.

159
00:09:36,476 --> 00:09:40,414
Tokuda-san is also very brave and cool →

160
00:09:40,480 --> 00:09:43,417
The defense attorney, Mr. Komiya, is also great.

161
00:09:43,483 --> 00:09:45,419
Do you mean "unfriendly intellectual"?

162
00:09:45,485 --> 00:09:48,422
>> Really, anyone is fine.

163
00:09:48,488 --> 00:09:52,993
(Manami) I only fall in love with the person I deserve.

164
00:09:54,494 --> 00:09:58,498
>> No, that's not convincing. (Manami) Huh?

165
00:10:00,500 --> 00:10:02,502
>> Huh…｡

166
00:10:04,004 --> 00:10:08,442
But, well, just keep it to yourself →

167
00:10:08,508 --> 00:10:11,445
Isn't it better than throwing your life at risk?

168
00:10:11,511 --> 00:10:15,949
(Manami) Does that mean you have someone important to you?

169
00:10:16,016 --> 00:10:19,519
>> I wonder if it was important...

170
00:10:21,021 --> 00:10:23,023
I don't understand.

171
00:10:25,025 --> 00:10:30,530
At least it wasn't taken seriously.

172
00:10:32,532 --> 00:10:35,969
(Manami) Ha, that's the worst.

173
00:10:37,971 --> 00:10:41,908
>> My friend got pregnant →

174
00:10:41,975 --> 00:10:45,912
It finally broke out.

175
00:10:45,979 --> 00:10:49,483
(Manami) And him?

176
00:10:51,485 --> 00:10:55,422
>> He was stabbed half to death.

177
00:10:55,489 --> 00:10:58,992
(Manami) That's not good.

178
00:11:03,497 --> 00:11:09,436
(Manami) After all, when someone important to you gets hurt →

179
00:11:09,503 --> 00:11:13,440
Doesn't it usually hurt a lot?

180
00:11:13,507 --> 00:11:18,512
It feels like my mind and body are being torn apart...

181
00:11:20,514 --> 00:11:24,951
>> I was surprised ha...

182
00:11:25,018 --> 00:11:28,455
It was too painful.

183
00:11:28,522 --> 00:11:30,524
Huh...

184
00:11:34,027 --> 00:11:37,464
I did it myself.

185
00:11:41,468 --> 00:11:44,404
(Yuriko's voice) Why were you at the scene?

186
00:11:44,471 --> 00:11:46,973
An address was sent to me by a person claiming to be Ai-chan→

187
00:11:47,040 --> 00:11:48,975
I was instructed to come.

188
00:11:49,042 --> 00:11:51,545
(Takamine) I see.

189
00:11:53,547 --> 00:11:55,549
what?

190
00:11:58,552 --> 00:12:00,987
As per Manami’s testimony →

191
00:12:01,054 --> 00:12:04,491
The person who met Detective Kuroiwa was Mr. Kiryu →

192
00:12:04,558 --> 00:12:07,994
Assuming that he took Detective Kuroiwa into custody →

193
00:12:08,061 --> 00:12:10,997
What are the benefits of sending messages to two people?

194
00:12:11,064 --> 00:12:13,500
Where is it?

195
00:12:13,567 --> 00:12:16,503
Do you mean to say that we made it ourselves?

196
00:12:16,570 --> 00:12:18,505
(Takamine) It's a matter of possibility.

197
00:12:18,572 --> 00:12:22,008
It's a huge misconception though!

198
00:12:22,075 --> 00:12:26,580
I thought my heart and body were going to be torn apart.

199
00:12:29,082 --> 00:12:31,518
(Iori's voice) When you can't protect someone important to you →

200
00:12:31,585 --> 00:12:33,520
This is what will happen.

201
00:12:33,587 --> 00:12:37,023
Manami has been in even more pain than this.

202
00:12:38,525 --> 00:12:40,460
(Yuriko) You know.

203
00:12:40,527 --> 00:12:43,463
How much do we care about Manami-chan?

204
00:12:43,530 --> 00:12:48,034
Because I think it's important! …is.

205
00:12:50,036 --> 00:12:53,974
Manami's actions of killing people around her are →

206
00:12:54,040 --> 00:12:56,476
It seems like a kind of obsession.

207
00:12:56,543 --> 00:13:00,614
(Yuriko) So, have the people at My Love looked into it?

208
00:13:00,680 --> 00:13:02,616
They even stormed the detention center.

209
00:13:02,682 --> 00:13:05,118
Isn't that also called obsession?

210
00:13:05,185 --> 00:13:06,119
it is….

211
00:13:06,186 --> 00:13:09,623
If you have any doubts, do it thoroughly!!

212
00:13:09,689 --> 00:13:13,693
If you do something half-hearted like that, you won't be able to protect anyone.

213
00:13:18,198 --> 00:13:20,634
(noise)

214
00:13:20,700 --> 00:13:24,638
(Rie) Huh… hah…｡

215
00:13:24,704 --> 00:13:27,641
(Manami) Hey, what are you doing!?

216
00:13:27,707 --> 00:13:29,643
No! >> Let go!

217
00:13:29,709 --> 00:13:32,145
(Manami) No!! >> Let go!! (Manami) Don't let go!

218
00:13:32,212 --> 00:13:34,581
Wait a minute...

219
00:13:34,648 --> 00:13:38,585
What are you doing? >> It doesn't matter, you'll die on your own →

220
00:13:38,652 --> 00:13:41,087
Leave me alone! (Manami) No!!

221
00:13:41,154 --> 00:13:43,089
>> It doesn't matter! To you.

222
00:13:43,156 --> 00:13:46,593
(Manami) Even if it doesn't matter, I want to stop it!

223
00:13:46,660 --> 00:13:49,596
If I can stop it...

224
00:13:49,663 --> 00:13:54,100
Because I couldn't stop it at all.

225
00:13:54,167 --> 00:13:58,104
An important person gets hurt.

226
00:13:58,171 --> 00:14:02,609
>> I'm not important, right?

227
00:14:02,676 --> 00:14:05,111
(cry)

228
00:14:05,178 --> 00:14:08,114
The boyfriend who tried to kill me →

229
00:14:08,181 --> 00:14:13,119
They didn't care about me in the slightest.→

230
00:14:13,186 --> 00:14:19,125
It worked out great for me!

231
00:14:19,192 --> 00:14:23,630
The truth is, even if I search all over the world →

232
00:14:23,697 --> 00:14:27,133
There's no one to take care of me.

233
00:14:27,200 --> 00:14:29,135
(cry)

234
00:14:29,202 --> 00:14:32,205
Because I fall in love...

235
00:14:35,141 --> 00:14:38,645
I'm so excited...

236
00:14:40,146 --> 00:14:43,583
(Manami) Wait a moment.

237
00:14:43,650 --> 00:14:49,089
You know, love is something even more wonderful.

238
00:14:49,155 --> 00:14:52,659
>> What's so great about that!

239
00:14:54,661 --> 00:14:57,163
Just say it!

240
00:15:00,166 --> 00:15:04,104
(Manami) The wonderful thing about love is →

241
00:15:04,170 --> 00:15:07,107
That means you can do it as many times as you like.

242
00:15:07,173 --> 00:15:11,111
>> You don't have to do it over and over again.

243
00:15:11,177 --> 00:15:13,613
(Manami) All over the world →

244
00:15:13,680 --> 00:15:19,119
There are countless great people out there.

245
00:15:19,185 --> 00:15:22,122
(Manami's voice) Each person is really important→

246
00:15:22,188 --> 00:15:26,626
Important people who will never be forgotten.

247
00:15:26,693 --> 00:15:32,132
Well, there are some loves that I want to forget.

248
00:15:32,198 --> 00:15:38,571
That kind of thing won't go away at all, though.→

249
00:15:38,638 --> 00:15:41,574
That's it →

250
00:15:41,641 --> 00:15:45,145
It has shaped me into the person I am today.

251
00:15:47,147 --> 00:15:53,153
So...it's okay to fall in love! Any amount.

252
00:15:55,155 --> 00:16:01,594
>> I can't do that... over and over again! Like you.

253
00:16:01,661 --> 00:16:06,099
(Manami) It doesn't matter if it's done zero times.

254
00:16:06,166 --> 00:16:09,102
>>Which one is it...?

255
00:16:09,169 --> 00:16:13,106
(Manami) I wonder how to be happy →

256
00:16:13,173 --> 00:16:15,608
Because there are as many as you want.

257
00:16:15,675 --> 00:16:17,610
(Manami's voice) If I were alive...

258
00:16:17,677 --> 00:16:20,113
As long as I'm alive... (Kuroiwa) [As long as I'm alive→

259
00:16:20,180 --> 00:16:22,615
Any amount...]

260
00:16:22,682 --> 00:16:35,061
♪～

261
00:16:35,128 --> 00:16:38,064
(cry)

262
00:16:38,131 --> 00:16:41,568
Huh...

263
00:16:41,634 --> 00:16:44,137
Sharakusa.

264
00:16:47,140 --> 00:16:49,142
I'm going to sleep now.

265
00:16:53,146 --> 00:16:56,649
(Manami) Tomorrow... I'll wake you up!

266
00:16:58,151 --> 00:17:01,588
>> It's okay... I'll wake up myself.

267
00:17:01,654 --> 00:17:21,107
♪～

268
00:17:21,174 --> 00:17:23,610
(Emoto) I can't sit still.

269
00:17:23,676 --> 00:17:28,114
An important lover lays hands on an important friend →

270
00:17:28,181 --> 00:17:30,683
I don't want to believe it.

271
00:17:32,685 --> 00:17:36,689
Is there anything I can do?

272
00:17:42,195 --> 00:17:45,131
(Tokuta) Mr. 25.

273
00:17:45,198 --> 00:17:47,634
Mr. 25.

274
00:17:47,700 --> 00:17:50,136
Number 25! >> Hey.

275
00:17:50,203 --> 00:17:52,205
(Manami) Hmm... Ah, yes.

276
00:17:55,008 --> 00:17:57,177
(Police car siren)

277
00:17:57,243 --> 00:18:01,181
(Manami) Is it true that you were released? (Takamine) Yes.

278
00:18:01,748 --> 00:18:04,184
(Manami) Why all of a sudden?

279
00:18:04,250 --> 00:18:08,188
>> We were able to obtain testimony denying Manami's involvement in the crime.

280
00:18:08,254 --> 00:18:10,757
(Manami) Who gave the testimony?

281
00:18:19,265 --> 00:18:21,201
(Kiryu) It's been a while.

282
00:18:21,267 --> 00:18:25,205
(Manami) A wanted criminal... I have to catch him.

283
00:18:25,271 --> 00:18:28,274
>> Hey hey hey hey hey hey…!

284
00:18:30,276 --> 00:18:32,712
(Manami) You pretended to be dead.

285
00:18:32,779 --> 00:18:35,715
>>Actually, I almost died.

286
00:18:35,782 --> 00:18:38,718
(Kiryu's voice) I was attacked on my way back from the temple.

287
00:18:38,785 --> 00:18:54,667
♪～

288
00:18:54,734 --> 00:18:57,170
(Kiryu's voice) I narrowly escaped, but→

289
00:18:57,237 --> 00:19:01,174
It was only a matter of time before he was killed unless he caught Ai-chan.

290
00:19:01,241 --> 00:19:03,743
(Manami) So you pretended to be dead?

291
00:19:05,245 --> 00:19:10,250
(Kiryu's voice) Yes, go back to your hometown... and get a witness.

292
00:19:11,751 --> 00:19:14,187
(Kiryu's voice) To Manami whom I met just before →

293
00:19:14,254 --> 00:19:17,190
I have to make you completely believe that I'm dead →

294
00:19:17,257 --> 00:19:21,194
I even wrote a will.

295
00:19:21,261 --> 00:19:24,697
(Manami) I thought he was still alive after all.

296
00:19:24,764 --> 00:19:26,699
>> Seriously?

297
00:19:26,766 --> 00:19:30,270
(Manami) The will was too messy.

298
00:19:31,771 --> 00:19:34,774
>> No, I was quite sincere.

299
00:19:36,276 --> 00:19:39,212
(Manami) Later→

300
00:19:39,279 --> 00:19:42,715
It would be a shame if it was broken so easily.

301
00:19:42,782 --> 00:19:47,220
Constraints >> Constraints?

302
00:19:47,287 --> 00:19:52,792
(Manami) We promise to live together even if we break up.

303
00:19:58,231 --> 00:20:01,734
>>Yeah...it won't break.

304
00:20:04,237 --> 00:20:08,174
(Manami) Did you notice? Ai-chan's true identity.

305
00:20:08,241 --> 00:20:10,176
>> When you and I tangled →

306
00:20:10,243 --> 00:20:12,679
Looks like Ai-chan dropped some of his belongings.

307
00:20:12,745 --> 00:20:15,181
I just picked it up.

308
00:20:15,248 --> 00:20:17,183
(Manami) Belongings?

309
00:20:17,250 --> 00:20:18,685
📱 [Vibration sound]

310
00:20:18,751 --> 00:20:23,189
(Kiryu's voice) I contacted Souma-kun so he could look into it.

311
00:20:23,256 --> 00:20:26,693
The moment I showed it to him, it seemed to click.

312
00:20:26,759 --> 00:20:28,695
(Kuroiwa) [I'll catch it]

313
00:20:28,761 --> 00:20:30,196
>> [Eh? ]

314
00:20:30,263 --> 00:20:34,200
(Kuroiwa) [I don't want to see it anymore]

315
00:20:34,267 --> 00:20:36,703
[Manami's hurt face]

316
00:20:36,769 --> 00:20:40,773
>> [If something happens to you, it will hurt even more]

317
00:20:43,276 --> 00:20:48,281
(Kuroiwa) [Then...Kiryu-san will definitely catch me]

318
00:20:51,784 --> 00:20:54,721
(Kuroiwa) [Take this and run away now]

319
00:20:56,222 --> 00:20:58,725
[Please go quickly! ]

320
00:21:04,731 --> 00:21:07,233
>> [Never die]

321
00:21:12,739 --> 00:21:16,242
Did the culprit know and was arrested on purpose?

322
00:21:18,244 --> 00:21:22,181
(Manami) I needed time to sort things out.

323
00:21:22,248 --> 00:21:26,252
Also... I wish it was different.

324
00:21:31,257 --> 00:21:34,694
(Manami) I have to go...

325
00:21:34,761 --> 00:21:38,765
>> Ai-chan's place? (Manami) Yes.

326
00:21:41,267 --> 00:21:45,204
>> Souma-kun's location is being lured out.

327
00:21:45,271 --> 00:21:48,207
(Manami's voice) Who's playing it?

328
00:21:48,274 --> 00:21:50,777
(Kiryu's voice) Souma-kun's friend.

329
00:21:52,278 --> 00:21:55,148
I should be heading to the hospital now.

330
00:21:55,214 --> 00:21:57,150
Let's hurry.

331
00:21:57,216 --> 00:21:58,718
(Manami) Yes.

332
00:22:00,219 --> 00:22:03,156
(sound of running)

333
00:22:03,222 --> 00:22:05,658
Thank you for your flexible response. >> No.

334
00:22:05,725 --> 00:22:08,161
Takamine is amazing right now.

335
00:22:08,227 --> 00:22:12,231
I can't really describe it, but it's supple and strong.

336
00:22:13,733 --> 00:22:15,668
That's awesome.

337
00:22:15,735 --> 00:22:17,670
(Manami) Let's go.

338
00:22:17,737 --> 00:22:19,739
>> Well then.

339
00:22:22,241 --> 00:22:26,179
Those two are really good.

340
00:22:26,245 --> 00:23:12,225
♪～
